-- China shares halt losing streak on solid earnings 
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Tue Apr 29, 2014 03:08AM EDT
-- None



BEIJING, April 29 (Reuters) - China's two main indexes broke four-day losing streaks on Tuesday, as a strong earnings report from insurance giant Ping An spurred solid gains.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended up 0.84 percent at 2020.34 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings rose 1.1 percent. Ping An Insurance Group of China Co Ltd <601318.SS> had a strong impact on both indexes after it reported a 46 percent rise in first-quarter profit, sending its shares up 2.6 percent. [ID:nL3N0NF0XF] Datong Coal Industry Co Ltd <601001.SS> shares jumped 10 percent, their biggest one-day gain in nine months, after the company reported a 1.04 billion yuan ($166.32 million) first-quarter profit.